    "# We always start with appropriate imports; note the use of the IPython magic\n",
    "# command to set up Matplotlib within the notebook\n",

   "source": [
    "## 4. Euler's equation\n",
    "\n",
    "### Question 1"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 2,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Specify step size and simulation length\n",
    "dx = 0.5\n",
    "total_x = 20\n",
    "N = int(total_x/dx)\n",
    "x = np.linspace(0,total_x,N+1) # Store end point \n",
    "# Initial condition\n",
    "y0 = 1.0\n",
    "# Define k\n",
    "k = 1.2\n",
    "y = np.zeros(N+1)\n",
    "y0 = 1.0\n",
    "y[0] = y0\n",
    "for i in range(N):\n",
    "    y[i+1] = y[i]+dx*(-k*y[i])"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### Question 2"
   ]
  },

  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "The effect of $\\Delta x$ is exactly as in the notes: and a value around 0.1 is just about OK\n",
    "\n",
    "### Question 3\n",
    "\n",
    "Note that I've chosen to allow an arbitrary size vector y; it would be fine to code this for the simple two component situation that we will be dealing with."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 6,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "def euler_solver(fun,y0,dt,N):\n",
    "    \"\"\"Solve dy/dt = fun(y,t) using Euler's method.\n",
    "    Inputs:\n",
    "    fun  f(y,t)\n",
    "    y0   Initial condition\n",
    "    dt   Step size\n",
    "    N    Number of steps\n",
    "    Returns: array of length N+1 with values of y\n",
    "    \"\"\"\n",
    "    retval = np.zeros((N+1,len(y0)))\n",
    "    retval[0] = y0\n",
    "    t = 0\n",
    "    for i in range(N):\n",
    "        t += dt\n",
    "        retval[i+1] = retval[i] + dt*fun(t,retval[i])\n",
    "    return retval"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### Question 4\n",
    "\n",
    "We need to define the function (RHS of the equation) and then call it"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 7,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "def RHS_SHO(t,y):\n",
    "    \"\"\"Return acceleration of SHO, defines k & m internally\"\"\"\n",
    "    k = 1.0\n",
    "    m = 1.0\n",
    "    x = y[0]\n",
    "    v = y[1]\n",
    "    dx = v\n",
    "    dv = -k*x/m\n",
    "    return np.array([dx,dv])"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 8,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {

      ]
     },
     "execution_count": 8,
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "execute_result"
    },

     "data": {
      "image/png": "\n",

       "<Figure size 432x288 with 1 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "motion = euler_solver(RHS_SHO,[1.0,0.0],0.01,1000)\n",
    "plt.plot(motion[:,0])\n",
    "plt.xlabel('Time')\n",
    "plt.ylabel('Displacement')\n",
    "plt.title('SHO motion from Euler solver')"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Note that a larger step size (I started with 0.1) gives an unstable solution which grows with time."
   ]

  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 5. Beyond Euler\n",
    "\n",
    "### Question 1"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 9,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "def RK4_solver(fun,y0,dt,N):\n",
    "    \"\"\"Solve dy/dt = fun(y,t) using fourth-order RK method.\n",
    "    Inputs:\n",
    "    fun  f(y,t)\n",
    "    y0   Initial condition - assumed to be two-component\n",
    "    dt   Step size\n",
    "    N    Number of steps\n",
    "    Returns: two arrays of length N+1 (x and v or equivalent)\n",
    "    \"\"\"\n",
    "    x = np.zeros(N+1)\n",
    "    v = np.zeros(N+1)\n",
    "    x[0] = y0[0]\n",
    "    v[0] = y0[1]\n",
    "    t = 0\n",
    "    y = y0\n",
    "    for i in range(N):\n",
    "        k1 = dt*fun(y,t)\n",
    "        k2 = dt*fun(y+0.5*k1,t+0.5*dt)\n",
    "        k3 = dt*fun(y+0.5*k2,t+0.5*dt)\n",
    "        k4 = dt*fun(y+k3,t+dt)\n",
    "        y=y+(k1+2*k2+2*k3+k4)/6\n",
    "        x[i+1] = y[0]\n",
    "        v[i+1] = y[1]\n",
    "    return x, v"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### Question 2"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 10,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "def RHS_linear_pendulum(y,t):\n",
    "    \"\"\"Implements linear pendulum RHS for ODE solver\"\"\"\n",
    "    g = 9.8\n",
    "    L = 1.0\n",
    "    x = y[0]\n",
    "    v = y[1]\n",
    "    dx = v\n",
    "    dv = -g*x/L\n",
    "    return np.array([dx,dv])"
   ]
  },

   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 11,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [

   "source": [
    "dt = 0.1\n",
    "total_t = 20\n",
    "N = int(total_t/dt)\n",
    "lin_p_x, lin_p_v = RK4_solver(RHS_linear_pendulum,[0.1*np.pi,0.0],dt,N)\n",
    "t = np.arange(0,total_t+0.00001,dt)\n",
    "plt.plot(t,lin_p_x)"

    "\n",
    "## 6. Boundary value problems\n",
    "\n",
    "### Question 1"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 12,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "def ball_vertical_RHS(y,t):\n",
    "    \"\"\"Calculate RHS for projectile ODE\"\"\"\n",
    "    x = y[0]\n",
    "    v = y[1]\n",
    "    dx = v\n",
    "    dv = -g\n",
    "    return np.array([dx,dv])"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 13,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "Initial velocity required is  49.04999999999995\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "g  = 9.81 # m/s^2\n",
    "t0 = 0.0  # s\n",
    "t1 = 10.0 # s\n",
    "dt = 0.05 # s\n",
    "N  = int((t1-t0)/dt)\n",
    "v_guess_1 = 0   # m/s\n",
    "v_guess_2 = 200 # m/s\n",
    "\n",
    "h1, vtmp = RK4_solver(ball_vertical_RHS,[0.0,v_guess_1],dt,N)\n",
    "h2, vtmp = RK4_solver(ball_vertical_RHS,[0.0,v_guess_2],dt,N)\n",
    "tol = 1e-4\n",
    "err = h2[N] - h1[N]\n",
    "while err > tol:\n",
    "    v_new = v_guess_2 - h2[N]*(v_guess_2 - v_guess_1)/(h2[N] - h1[N])\n",
    "    err = abs(v_guess_1 - v_guess_2)\n",
    "    v_guess_1 = v_guess_2\n",
    "    v_guess_2 = v_new\n",
    "    h1, vtmp = RK4_solver(ball_vertical_RHS,[0.0,v_guess_1],dt,N)\n",
    "    h2, vtmp = RK4_solver(ball_vertical_RHS,[0.0,v_guess_2],dt,N)\n",
    "print(\"Initial velocity required is \",v_new)"
   ]
  },
